shire, at a High Court hearing in London today.\u00a0<\/p>\n<p>[embed id=\"embed_1\"]<\/p>\n<p>A barrister representing Anderson told Judge Jaron Lewis that the advert, displayed on a website in February 2021, suggested he was \u201cprotective of or sympathetic to the abuse of children and those who perpetrate such abuse\u201d.<\/p>\n<p>Felicity McMahon said Anderson had settled a \u201cthreatened action\u201d for defamation and breach of data protection law and rights with Google Ireland.<\/p>\n<p>Barrister Hope Williams, who represented Google Ireland, said the company \u201csincerely\u201d apologised to Anderson for any distress the advert had caused him.<\/p>\n<p>Ms Williams told the judge that the advert should not have been displayed as it did not comply with Google Ads policies.<\/p>\n<p>[embed id=\"embed_2\"]<\/p>\n<p>She added that the advert was removed as soon as Mr Anderson alerted Google Ireland to it.<\/p>\n","permalink":"https:\/\/www.thejournal.ie\/lee-anderson-mp-settlement-google-advert-5706779-Mar2022\/","shortlink":"https:\/\/jrnl.ie\/5706779","type":"post","secondary_publications":[],"main_story_links":[{"text":"","url":""},{"text":"","url":""}],"categories":{"thejournal":{"id":"2","name":"International","slug":"international"}},"publication_data":{"primary":"thejournal","all":["thejournal"],"categories":{"thejournal":[{"id":"1","name":"Irish","slug":"irish"},{"id":"2","name":"International","slug":"international"}]}},"images":{"thumbnail":{"image":"https:\/\/c2.thejournal.ie\/media\/2022\/03\/lee-anderson-court-hearing-145x145.jpg","width":145,"height":145},"medium":{"image":"https:\/\/c2.thejournal.ie\/media\/2022\/03\/lee-anderson-court-hearing-296x394.jpg","width":296,"height":394},"large":{"image":"https:\/\/c2.thejournal.ie\/media\/2022\/03\/lee-anderson-court-hearing-630x840.jpg","width":630,"height":840},"larger":{"image":"https:\/\/c2.thejournal.ie\/media\/2022\/03\/lee-anderson-court-hearing-558x744.jpg","width":558,"height":744},"rive