mation","slug":"goodinformation","label":"The Good Information Project","copy":"Get regular updates from The Good Information Project, a new initiative from TheJournal.ie to start a conversation with our readers about critical issues facing our country."},"retargeting":[{"key":"irish_audience","bucket_ttl":7776000,"threshold":1,"threshold_window":604800},{"key":"irish_audience","bucket_ttl":7776000,"threshold":1,"threshold_window":604800}],"id_name":"article","primary_image":{"id":5693974,"object_id":5693974,"object_type":"article","crops":["original"],"credit":{"text":false,"url":false},"version":5694254},"time_label":{"is_displayed":true,"is_replaced":false,"replacement_text":null}},{"id":5680452,"title":"Publishers aim to 'break Google's stranglehold' over advertising with antitrust complaint ","slug":"google-antitrust-complaint","date":"2022-02-11 10:58:20","date_modified":"2022-02-11 12:20:04","date_published":"2022-02-11 10:58:20","is_updated":false,"has_audio":"0","has_video":"0","has_slideshow":"0","is_hot_on_twitter":"0","publication":"thejournal","stats":{"views":"7458","facebook":"4","comments":"4","twitter":"0","email":"0","dislikes":"0","likes":"0","fresh_until_ts":1648342910},"syndication_source":"","seo_title":null,"seo_description":null,"is_sponsored":0,"sticky":null,"header_url":null,"internal_syndication_id":null,"digest_key":"article_5680452","date_unix":1644577100,"date_modified_unix":1644582004,"status":"publish","is_exclusive":"0","excerpt":"The European Publishers Council has lodged the complaint with the European Commission.","content":"<p>A GROUP REPRESENTING some of the largest media organisations in Europe has filed an antitrust complaint against Google, with the express aim of \u201cbreaking the stranglehold\u201d the search engine giant holds over online advertising.\u00a0<\/p>\n<p>The European Publishers Council (EPC) has lodged the complaint with the European Commission which it is appealing to \u201cto hold\u00a0Google\u00a0accountable for its\u00a0anticompetitive\u00a0conduct\u201d over ad tech.<\/p>\n<p>The EPC is asking for the Commission to impose remedies to restore \u201ceffective competition\u201d in the\u00a0ad\u00a0tech\u00a0value chain for press publishers and other businesses.\u00a0<\/p>\n<p>EPC members include Bauer Media Group \u2013 which owns\u00a0<em>Newstalk<\/em> \u2013 and <em>Daily Mail<\/em> publisher DMG Media. The <em>Guardian<\/em> and <em>The<\/em>\u00a0<em>New York Times<\/em> are also members.<\/p>\n<p>[embed id=\"embed_1\"]<\/p>\n<p>The antitrust complaint is the <a href=\"https:\/\/www.theguardian.com\/technology\/blog\/2005\/dec\/07\/europeanpublis\" target=\"_blank\">latest in a long running battle<\/a> between publishers and Google, which has Dublin as its European headquarters.\u00a0<\/p>\n<p>\u201cIt is high time for the European Commission to impose measures on\u00a0Google\u00a0that actually change, not just challenge, its behaviour,\u201d\u00a0EPC Chairman Christian Van Thillo said.<\/p>\n<p>He alleged that Google\u2019s behaviour has \u201ccaused and continues to cause considerable harm, not just to Europe\u2019s press publishers, but to all advertisers\u201d.\u00a0<\/p>\n<p>This will \u201ceventually\u201d land on consumers in the form of higher prices and less choice, Thillo added.<\/p>\n<p>\u201cCompetition authorities across the world have found that\u00a0Google\u00a0has restricted competition in\u00a0ad\u00a0tech, yet\u00a0Google\u00a0has been able to get away with minor commitments which do nothing to bring about any meaningful changes to its conduct.<\/p>\n<p>\u201cThis cannot go on. The stakes are too high, particularly for the future viability of funding a free and pluralistic press. We call on the Commission to take concrete steps right now that will actually break the stranglehold that\u00a0Google\u00a0has over us all.\u201d<\/p>\n<p>[embed id=\"embed_2\"]<\/p>\n<p>In a statement, the EPC said that since Google\u2019s acquisition of marketing platform DoubleClick in 2008,\u00a0the company \u201chas embarked on a barrage\u201d of tactics to \u201cforeclose competition in\u00a0ad\u00a0tech\u201d.\u00a0<\/p>\n<p>He continued: \u201cThis strategy paid off, and\u00a0Google\u00a0has achieved end-to-end control of the\u00a0ad\u00a0tech\u00a0value chain, boasting market shares as high as 90-100% in segments of the\u00a0ad\u00a0tech\u00a0chain.\u201d<\/p>\n<p>As Google \u201crepresents the buyer and the seller in the same transaction\u201d, he alleged there are conflicts of interest in how it operates.<\/p>\n<p>The EPC insisted that the European Commission is well positioned to act on its complaint, as it can leverage the findings of a number of competition authorities, in France, the UK and Australia.\u00a0<\/p>\n<p>Van Thillo said: \u201cThis\u00a0Complaint\u00a0presents a unique opportunity for the European Commission to rectify the problems that have arisen as a direct result of its 2008 clearance of the\u00a0Google\/DoubleClick merger, by imposing effective remedies that will restore competition in\u00a0ad\u00a0tech, for the benefit of European press publishers, marketers, and consumers.\u201d<\/p>\n","permalink":"https:\/\/www.thejournal.ie\/google-antitrust-complaint-5680452-Feb2022\/","shortlink":"https:\/\/jrnl.ie\/5680452","type":"post","secondary_publications":[],"main_story_links":[{"text":"","url":""},{"text":"","url":""}],"categories":{"thejournal":{"id":"1","name":"Irish","slug":"irish"}},"publication_data":{"primary":"thejournal","all":["thejournal"],"categories":{"thejournal":[{"id":"1","name":"Irish","slug":"irish"}]}},"images":{"thumbnail":{"image":"https:\/\/c1.thejournal.ie\/media\/2022\/02\/google-86-145x145.jpg","width":145,"height":145},"medium":{"image":"https:\/\/c1.thejournal.ie\/media\/2022\/02\/google-86-296x193.jpg","width":296,"height":193},"large":{"image":"https:\/\/c1.thejournal.ie\/media\/2022\/02\/google-86-630x410.jpg","width":630,"height":410},"larger":{"image":"https:\/\/c1.thejo